                  <additions>
                    <list>
                    <item xml:id = "a1">
                      <desc>
                    <locus target = "#iv"/> The first few words of the hymn to Mary, “The angels praise Mary,” <foreign xml:lang = "gez">ይዌድስዋ፡ መላእክት፡ ለማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a2">
                    <desc>
                      <locus target = "#65v"/> A symbol and the word <foreign xml:lang = "gez">መንፈቀ፡</foreign> mark the midpoint of the Psalms
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a3">
                    <desc type = "OwnershipNote">
                      Note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang = "amh">ልጅ፡ ይገረሙ፡</foreign>, in a crude hand, <locus target = "#ir"/>
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a4">
                    <desc type = "OwnershipNote">Note of ownership by <foreign xml:lang = "gez">አድማሡ</foreign>, <locus target = "#171r"/></desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a5">
                    <desc>
                      Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (ff. 51v, 77v, 80v, 98r); and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (ff. 4r, 21r, 71r, 79rv, 85v, 108r, 121v)
                    </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "a6">
                    <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an
                      appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout). This scribe will also reduce the font
                      size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target = "#43r #43v #44r #45r #44v"/>, etc.)
                    </desc>
                  </item>

                  <item xml:id = "e1">
                    <desc>
                    The general condition of the parchment is moderately dirty and relatively unworn. The parchment is fairly consistent and relatively thick
                  </desc>
                  </item>
                  <item xml:id = "e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target = "#151v"/> erased
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
